"""
batch_ss_monte_carlo.py
=======================
Batch Safety Stock Monte Carlo — generalises the single-SKU JJA simulation
across multiple product × location intersections pulled live from Snowflake.

Quintile-aware OOS tolerance
-----------------------------
  Q1  — max 1 OOS day acceptable (highest priority)
  Q2  — max 1 OOS day acceptable
  Q3  — max 3 OOS days acceptable
  Q4  — max 4 OOS days acceptable
  Q5  — max 4 OOS days acceptable
  NULL— treated as Q3 (max 3 OOS days)

The recommended SS is the minimum number of coverage days where at least
TARGET_SL (default 95%) of simulation paths have ≤ oos_tolerance OOS days.

Architecture
------------
  DataFetcher      — pulls demand, fill rates, delivery cadence, case size,
                     current Kinaxis SS policy, and quintile flags per pair
  SimulationEngine — DOW-aware (s,S) Monte Carlo (vectorised, numpy)
  BatchRunner      — orchestrates the loop, handles errors, writes output

Inputs
------
  candidates.csv   — two columns: product_id, location_id
                     (or pass --auto-candidates to pull all-quintile pairs
                      from the specified sites directly)

Outputs
-------
  results/ss_batch_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.csv
  results/ss_batch_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.xlsx  (Summary + Full Sweep tabs)

Usage
-----
  # Auto-pull all quintile candidates for specified sites:
  python batch_ss_monte_carlo.py \\
    --user you@gopuff.com \\
    --auto-candidates \\
    --location-ids 258,37,690,265,99

  # From a candidates CSV file:
  python batch_ss_monte_carlo.py \\
    --user you@gopuff.com \\
    --candidates candidates.csv

  # Tune simulation parameters:
  python batch_ss_monte_carlo.py \\
    --user you@gopuff.com \\
    --auto-candidates \\
    --lookback-days 120 \\
    --n-sims 5000 \\
    --target-sl 0.95 \\
    --ss-min 3 \\
    --ss-max 21

Dependencies
------------
  pip install snowflake-connector-python[pandas] numpy pandas openpyxl
"""

